yingyinNormal.en: Your health is my only concern.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你的健康是我唯一关心的。

yingyinNormal.en: You're reading your health book.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你在读你的健康常识课本。

yingyinNormal.en: What matters more? Health or power?
yingyinNormal.zh: 到底哪样更重要？健康还是权力？

yingyinNormal.en: These diet beverages still pose serious health risks.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但这些无糖饮料依旧威胁着你的健康。

yingyinNormal.en: Hello, I am Baymax, your personal health care companion.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你好，我是大白，您的私人健康助手。

yingyinNormal.en: Hello, I am Baymax, Your personal health care companion.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你好，我是大白，你的私人健康助手。

yingyinNormal.en: Hello, I am Baymax, your personal health care companion.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你好，我叫大白，是你的私人健康助手。

yingyinNormal.en: I trust your family is in good health, Miss Elizabeth?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我相信你一家人身体都健康吧 伊丽莎白小姐？

yingyinNormal.en: Tadashi was in excellent health. With a proper diet and exercise, he should have lived a long life.
yingyinNormal.zh: 阿正身体十分健康，饮食健康，坚持锻炼，他应该会长寿。

yingyinNormal.en: That's a whole lot of health. How many are there? Forty-four.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这样才健康，有多少种？四十四种。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah, but Mon that's totally different. He was you're health teacher.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是两回事，他是你的健康教育老师。

yingyinNormal.en: You've got love, you're in good health, you've got a roof over your head.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你拥有爱，你拥有健康的身体，你还拥有一个栖身之所。

yingyinNormal.en: You just couldn't hold it in, could you? Wait, she's your health care proxy?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你就是不能接受，是吧？等等，她是你的健康监护人？

yingyinNormal.en: Senator. My dad always said that Kentucky mash was the secret to health.
yingyinNormal.zh: 议员，我爸爸过去常说肯塔基的麦芽浆是永葆健康的秘诀。

yingyinNormal.en: It actually presumably if you keep on doing, and you're being a better health over the long time.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果你继续这么做，身体会一直很健康。

yingyinNormal.en: 10.9 million new jobs, 10 million more Americans with health insurance.
yingyinNormal.zh: 1090万新的就业岗位，1000多万有着健康保险的国人。

yingyinNormal.en: I need you to tell him to treat our Health class with dignity and sensitivity.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我想让你告诉他要带着尊重与敏感之心对待我们的健康课。

yingyinNormal.en: I am confident. Surely. I think the taste will deliver. The health aspect for sure.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我很有信心。我认为味道说明一切。在健康方面肯定没问题。

yingyinNormal.en: Baymax, you scanned him? I am programmed to assess everyone's health care needs.
yingyinNormal.zh: 大白，你扫描过他了? 我的程序设计我测定每个人的健康水平。

yingyinNormal.en: Obesity, the long-term health of our families in the country are at stake.
yingyinNormal.zh: 肥胖，在这个国家普遍存在的健康议题，而且已经到了堪称危急的时刻。

examination_example.sentence: Likewise, among the elderly, being somewhat overweight is often an indicator of good <highlight>health</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 同样，在老年人中，稍微超重往往是健康的一个标志。

examination_example.sentence: And there are <highlight>health</highlight> conditions for which being overweight is actually protective.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在一些健康状况下，超重实际上是有保护作用的。

examination_example.sentence: Meanwhile, it has more than $120 billion in unfunded liabilities, mostly for employee <highlight>health</highlight> and retirement costs.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 与此同时，它有超过1200亿美元的无资金准备的负债，其中大部分用于员工医疗和退休支出。

examination_example.sentence: Teachers, employers, and <highlight>health</highlight> professionals have been shown to harbor biases against the obese.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 教师、雇主和医疗专业人士对肥胖者存有偏见。

examination_example.sentence: Rosenberg argues convincingly that public-<highlight>health</highlight> advocates ought to take a page from advertisers, so skilled at applying peer pressure.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 罗森博格令人信服地指出，公共卫生倡导者应该向善于施加同伴压力的广告商学习。

examination_example.sentence: A move back to self-sufficiency, the argument goes, would boost the farming industry, political sovereignty and even the nation's <highlight>health</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这种观点认为，回归自给自足将促进农业发展、政治主权甚至国家正常运作。

word_usage.usage:
health表“健康”时，指人身体和精神上的“健康状况的(可好可坏)”，为不可数名词。
(1) "健康状况(不)好"用be in poor/ good heath表达，注意不加冠词。
示例：他身体很糟，是吗?
误 He is in a poor health, isn't he?
正 He is in poor health, isn't he?
(2) “...对身体(不)好”用good/ bad for one's health表达。
示例：吸烟对身体不好。
Smoking is not good for your health.

affix_sense_info.affix_sense_chinese: 名词后缀, 通常指抽象名词

word_usage.usage:
health表“健康”时，指人身体和精神上的“健康状况的(可好可坏)”，为不可数名词。
(1) "健康状况(不)好"用be in poor/ good heath表达，注意不加冠词。
示例：他身体很糟，是吗?
误 He is in a poor health, isn't he?
正 He is in poor health, isn't he?
(2) “...对身体(不)好”用good/ bad for one's health表达。
示例：吸烟对身体不好。
Smoking is not good for your health.
